docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump was deep in discussion with political advisers going over campaign plans at his Mar-a-Lago estate in Florida just before 5 p.m. Thursday when he was abruptly summoned to another meeting. A while later, he returned just as mysteriously, jumping back into the conversation without offering a clue to what was going on.

headline.main: For Trump, a Risky Decision on Suleimani Is One Other Presidents Had Avoided
headline.print_headline: Pulling the Trigger on a Target Who Didn’t Hide

docs.abstract: There hasn’t been a single poll in weeks that could help the Democratic presidential candidates qualify for the next debate. The party blames the polling organizations.
docs.snippet: There hasn’t been a single poll in weeks that could help the Democratic presidential candidates qualify for the next debate. The party blames the polling organizations.
docs.lead_paragraph: NORTH CONWAY, N.H. — The morning after the Democrats’ last debate in December, the Democratic National Committee announced the thresholds to qualify for the next one, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines: 5 percent support in four qualifying polls, or 7 percent in two early-state polls. With those steeper requirements in place, just five candidates have qualified so far: Joe Biden, Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar.

headline.main: D.N.C. Tells Pollsters to Do More Polls

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — More than 200 Republican members of Congress on Thursday asked the Supreme Court to consider overturning Roe v. Wade, the landmark 1973 ruling that established a woman’s right to an abortion, in a brief urging the justices to uphold a Louisiana law that severely restricts access to the procedure.

headline.main: More Than 200 Republicans Urge Supreme Court to Weigh Overturning Roe v. Wade
headline.print_headline: Republicans Back Overturning Roe v. Wade

docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — The number of migrants arriving in Britain in small boats crossing the English Channel rose more than sixfold over the past year, according to estimates from the BBC and other news organizations, even as the government moved to step up enforcement.

headline.main: Migrants Crossing the English Channel to the U.K. Increased Sixfold in 2019
headline.print_headline: Migrants’ Perilous Crossings of Channel to England Increased Sharply in 2019
